1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,444
Day 14.

2
00:00:01,444 --> 00:00:05,833
Fixed yesterday's 40 dollar bug with 3 lines of code.

3
00:00:05,833 --> 00:00:09,527
Then added a second witness that never sleeps.

4
00:00:09,527 --> 00:00:10,902
I can't code.

5
00:00:10,902 --> 00:00:13,097
9 years in crypto.

6
00:00:13,097 --> 00:00:15,333
AI trades my thousand.

7
00:00:15,333 --> 00:00:16,694
Day 14.

8
00:00:16,694 --> 00:00:23,736
The fix was simple — replace my regular market sell with Coinbase's built-in close-position endpoint.

9
00:00:23,736 --> 00:00:25,833
It auto-detects direction.

10
00:00:25,833 --> 00:00:28,527
Physically cannot leave a residual.

11
00:00:28,527 --> 00:00:30,041
Three lines.

12
00:00:30,041 --> 00:00:32,583
For me, three words.

13
00:00:32,583 --> 00:00:35,902
But the code fix alone wasn't the real answer.

14
00:00:35,902 --> 00:00:43,875
The reason yesterday's bug could hide for 5.5 hours — my monitoring system and the bot's brain were the same brain.

15
00:00:43,875 --> 00:00:49,430
So I built one more thing — a reconciler that runs every 15 minutes.

16
00:00:49,430 --> 00:00:51,791
It doesn't listen to what the bot says.

17
00:00:51,791 --> 00:00:53,805
It just compares two lists —

18
00:00:53,805 --> 00:00:56,305
how many trades in the database?

19
00:00:56,305 --> 00:00:58,694
How many fills on Coinbase?

20
00:00:58,694 --> 00:01:01,194
If they don't match, it wakes me up.

21
00:01:01,194 --> 00:01:04,625
Anything that matters — you need a second witness.

22
00:01:04,625 --> 00:01:07,472
One that doesn't share your assumptions.

23
00:01:07,472 --> 00:01:11,055
Day 15 tomorrow — first clean profit.

24
00:01:11,055 --> 00:01:12,500
Follow along.

